<section>
  <p>Experimenting with controller designs I ordered a flex sensor and threaded it into the finger of a longboard slide glove so the board could be controlled with the flex of my hand itself.</p>
  <p>After suffering water damage I ordered a new <acronym title="12 serial, 3 parallel cells">12s3p</acronym> battery from <a href="http://www.chiboards.com/">ChiBoards</a> allowing me to run the motors more efficiently with higher voltage. During this process I did a major overhaul cleaning up all the wiring and weatherproofing. The final build still includes the highest quality components from the initial build like the <a href="http://www.jetskateboards.com/">JET Deck</a>, <a href="http://www.ollinboardcompany.com/">Ollin</a> <acronym title="Vedder’s electronic speec controller">VESC</acronym>s, and <a href="http://www.carvonskates.com/">CarvOn</a> hub motors while adding components like a Castle <acronym title="battery elimenator circut">BEC</acronym> to run low voltage components, <a href="http://orangatangwheels.com/blog/orangatang-nipples/">Orangutan nipples</a> upgraded bushings, <a href="https://shredlights.com/">Shredlights</a>, and custom fabricated wiring harnesses.</p>
